\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 Greetings from Paul
\rem /s1 Salutation
\p
\v 1 \add This letter is from\add* Paul, one \add of Yeshua's\add* ambassadorsВҰ125555, not chosen by people or any humanВҰ125558 desire, butВҰ125562 chosen \add directly\add* by Yeshua the \nd messiahВҰ125565\nd* andВҰ125566 \nd GodВҰ125567\nd* the fatherВҰ125568 who raisedВҰ125570 Yeshua from the deadВҰ125574.
\v 2 \add On behalf of\add* all the believers here, \add I'm writing\add* to the assembliesВҰ125582 \add of believers\add* in GalatiaВҰ125584.
\p
\v 3 May youВҰ125586 all experience the graceВҰ125585 and peaceВҰ125588 that comes from \nd GodВҰ125590\nd* the fatherВҰ125591 and ourВҰ125595 \nd masterВҰ125594 Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ125597\nd*,
\v 4 the one who gaveВҰ125599 himselfВҰ125601 for our sinsВҰ125605 to rescueВҰ125608 us from this presentВҰ125615, evilВҰ125616 age, accordingВҰ125617 to \nd GodВҰ125621\nd* our father'sВҰ125623 desireвҖ”
\v 5 \add our father\add* who'll be praised even through future ages. That's how it is.
\s1 There's only one good message
\rem /s1 The One Gospel; One gospel for all; There Is Only One Good News; There Is No Other Gospel
\p
\v 6 I'm astounded that you \add people\add* have so quicklyВҰ125638 replaced the goodВҰ125650 messageВҰ125650 \add that you heard\add* from the one who calledВҰ125642 you to the \nd messiah\nd*'s graceВҰ125646. You've replaced it with anotherВҰ125649 narrative
\v 7 whichВҰ125651 is not at all anotherВҰ125654 good message, butВҰ125662 rather comes from those who are confusing you and wantingВҰ125663 to alterВҰ125664 the \add actual\add* good message about the \nd messiahВҰ125668\nd*.
\v 8 Even if either we ourselves or \add even\add* a messengerВҰ125675 from heavenВҰ125677 were to preach a different вҖҳgood messageвҖҷ which disagrees with the good message that we \add first\add* preached to you, then they shouldВҰ125687 be cursedВҰ125686.
\v 9 As we've previouslyВҰ125689 saidВҰ125689, and even now say it againВҰ125693: if anyoneВҰ125696 preachesВҰ125698 a вҖҳgoodВҰ125698 messageВҰ125698вҖҷ to you that's different from what you already heard, let that person be cursedВҰ125703.
\p
\v 10 Am I trying to please and persuadeВҰ125708 people or \nd GodВҰ125712\nd*? If I was stillВҰ125719 trying to please people, I wouldn't be \add worthy to be\add* one of the \nd messiah\nd*'s slavesВҰ125723.
\s1 Paul was commissioned directly by God
\rem /s1 Paul Called by God; Paul's Message Comes from Christ; How Paul Became an Apostle; Paul's Vindication of His Apostleship
\p
\v 11 I'm letting you know, brothersВҰ125731 andВҰ125731 sistersВҰ125731, thatВҰ125738 the good message I proclaimed didn'tВҰ125744 just come from humanВҰ125747 ideas.
\v 12 It didn't come from my ideas, nor was I taughtВҰ125757 it by some other person, but it was revealed to me by \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ125762\nd*.
\p
\v 13 \add Brothers and sisters,\add* you've heardВҰ125763 about my previous behaviour, when as a strict Jew, I was extreme in persecuting\x + \xo 1:13: \xt Acts 8:3; 22:4-5; 26:9-11.\x* the assemblyВҰ125777 of God's people, and was trying to destroy them.
\v 14 I was progressingВҰ125784 in JudaismВҰ125787\x + \xo 1:14: \xt Acts 22:3.\x* quicker than many of myВҰ125794 contemporariesВҰ125790, beingВҰ125798 so much more zealousВҰ125797 in observing our ancient traditionsВҰ125802.
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ125816 \add God\add*, who'd planned this from even before I was born,\x + \xo 1:15-16: \xt Acts 9:3-6; 22:6-10; 26:13-18.\x* calledВҰ125817 me, because of hisВҰ125821 graceВҰ125820,
\v 16 so that he could revealВҰ125822 hisВҰ125825 son through me, and I could preachВҰ125829 the goodВҰ125829 messageВҰ125829 to non-Jews. I didn'tВҰ125836 rush to get advice from others,
\v 17 nor did I head to Yerushalem to \add consult with\add* the ambassadorsВҰ125851 there that preceded me, butВҰ125856 I went away to ArabiaВҰ125855 and then later returnedВҰ125858 to DamascusВҰ125860.
\v 18 Then finally, afterВҰ125862 threeВҰ125864 yearsВҰ125863, I wentВҰ125866 to Yerushalem\x + \xo 1:18: \xt Acts 9:26-30.\x* to get to know Peter, andВҰ125873 stayed with himВҰ125877 for just over two weeks.
\v 19 I didn'tВҰ125884 meet any of the other ambassadorsВҰ125883, other than Yeshua's brotherВҰ125891, Yacob,
\v 20 andВҰ125895 what I'm writing to you, I'm writing with \nd GodВҰ125901\nd* watching, so I'm not lyingВҰ125904.
\p
\v 21 Then I wentВҰ125906 into the regionsВҰ125909 of SyriaВҰ125911 andВҰ125912 CiliciaВҰ125914.
\v 22 The assembliesВҰ125922 back in YudeaВҰ125925 thatВҰ125926 believe in the \nd messiahВҰ125928\nd* didn'tВҰ125917 know me by sight,
\v 23 butВҰ125930 had only heard about meвҖ”thatВҰ125942 the person who'd once been persecuting them was now preachingВҰ125939 the goodВҰ125939 messageВҰ125939 about the faithВҰ125941 himself,
\v 24 andВҰ125945 theyВҰ125946 praisedВҰ125946 \nd GodВҰ125950\nd* because of \add what had happened to\add* me.
\c 2
\s1 The ambassadors accept Paul and Barnabas
\rem /s1 The Apostles Accept Paul
\rem /s1 Paul Accepted by the Apostles
\rem /s1 Paul and the Other Apostles
\p
\v 1 It was fourteenВҰ125953 yearsВҰ125954 later that I made the uphill trek to Yerushalem\x + \xo 2:1: \xt Acts 11:30; 15:2.\x* with BarnabasВҰ125961, taking TitosВҰ125965 alongВҰ125963 as well.
\v 2 \add God\add* had told me to go there, and I explained to the \add leaders there\add* the goodВҰ125974 messageВҰ125974 that I'd been proclaimingВҰ125976 to the non-Jews. I did it privately, to double-check that I wasn't somehowВҰ125986 just acting vainly.
\v 3 But not even TitosВҰ125994, who was with me, was compelledВҰ126000 to be circumcisedВҰ126001, even though he's a GreekВҰ125998.
\v 4 However, some falseВҰ126006 brothersВҰ126006 were sneakedВҰ126005 in to monitor the freedomsВҰ126011 thatВҰ126013 weВҰ126014 have in the \nd messiahВҰ126017\nd*, \nd Yeshua\nd*, and theyВҰ126021 wanted us to be enslavedВҰ126021 to their traditions.
\v 5 But weВҰ126027 didn'tВҰ126024 submitВҰ126029 to them even for one hourВҰ126026, so that the truthВҰ126032 of the goodВҰ126035 messageВҰ126035 could continueВҰ126036 amongst youВҰ126039.
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 2:6: \xt Deu 10:17.\x*And those people who were supposed \add leaders\add* (although what they were didn't mean much to me, becauseВҰ126059 \nd GodВҰ126054\nd* doesn't go by appearancesВҰ126052) didn't really contributeВҰ126063 anything useful, as far as I could tell.
\v 7 Instead, they saw that I'veВҰ126069 been entrusted with taking the goodВҰ126071 messageВҰ126071 to the non-Jews, just like PeterВҰ126075 was entrusted to take it to the Jews,
\v 8 because the same \add God\add* who worked in PeterВҰ126081 to assign him to the Jews also worked in me \add to assign me\add* to the non-Jews.
\v 9 So, seeing the graceВҰ126096 that \add God\add* had shown towards me, Yacob and Peter and Yohan, the apparent pillarsВҰ126108 \add of the assemblies\add*, accepted me and BarnabasВҰ126114 as equals, so that weВҰ126117 could goВҰ126117 to the non-Jews and them to the Jews.
\v 10 Also, \add they said that\add* weВҰ126131 need to keep helping the poor, but I was eager to do that anyway.
\s1 Paul scolds Peter
\rem /s1 Paul Rebukes Peter at Antioch
\rem /s1 Paul Confronts Peter
\rem /s1 Paul Opposes Peter
\p
\v 11 But when Peter cameВҰ126140 to AntiochВҰ126144, I had to oppose himВҰ126147 to his faceВҰ126146, becauseВҰ126149 he'd messed up.
\v 12 He'd been eating with non-Jews, butВҰ126170 when Yacob and his companions arrived, he about-faced and started eating separately, becauseВҰ126154 he was afraid of \add being criticised by\add* the strict Jews.
\v 13 The other Jews with himВҰ126179 were also being hypocritesвҖ”so much so that even BarnabasВҰ126187 joined theirВҰ126190 hypocrisyвҖ”
\v 14 butВҰ126193 when I sawВҰ126195 that they weren't beingВҰ126213 honest with the truthВҰ126201 of the goodВҰ126203 messageВҰ126203, I had to say to Peter in front of everybody, вҖңIf you Jews are livingВҰ126220 more like non-Jews, and not like \add strict\add* Jews, how can you force non-Jews to obey all the Jewish traditions?вҖқ
\s1 You can't be saved by obeying rules
\rem /s1 Jews and Gentiles Are Saved by Faith
\p
\v 15 We follow Jewish laws, not other nations' customs,
\v 16 but we know that we're not saved by following rules,\x + \xo 2:16: a \xt Psa 143:2; Rom 3:20; \xo b \xt Rom 3:22.\x* but only by faith in Yeshua the messiah. So we've believedВҰ126258 in Yeshua the messiah so that we can be made guiltless by our faith in the messiah, and not by obeying all those rules, becauseВҰ126269 none of those rules can ever make any personВҰ126241 guiltless.
\v 17 However, if we attempt to be made guiltless through the messiah, yet find that we're sinnersВҰ126290, does that mean that the messiah is a servantВҰ126294 to sinВҰ126293? That could never be so!
\v 18 If I rebuild what I've already torn down, that would show me to be a law-breaker.
\v 19 \x + \xo 2:19: \xt Rom 6:1-11; 7:1-6.\x*It was the law that showed me that I needed die to the idea of following the law, so that I could liveВҰ126315 \add to serve\add* \nd GodВҰ126314\nd* \add instead\add*. I was executed on a post along with the \nd messiahВҰ126316\nd*,
\v 20 and I'm not living any more, butВҰ126319 it's the \nd messiahВҰ126326\nd* now living in me. The way thatВҰ126336 my bodyВҰ126332 stays alive now is by living by faithВҰ126334 in God's sonвҖ”the one who lovedВҰ126344 me and allowed himselfВҰ126348 to be executed for me.
\v 21 I'm not rejectingВҰ126352 God's graceВҰ126354, becauseВҰ126358 if the law could make me guiltless, that would mean that the \nd messiahВҰ126363\nd* diedВҰ126365 unnecessarily.
\c 3
\rem /s1 The freedom of faith
\rem /s1 Faith or Observance of the Law
\rem /s1 The Law and Faith in Christ
\rem /s1 Law or Faith
\p
\v 1 You foolishВҰ126367 GalatiansВҰ126368, who tricked youВҰ126370 into changing? You know that \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ126380\nd* was publiclyВҰ126381 known to have been executedВҰ126384 \add by being nailed to\add*\x + \xo 3:1: \xt Jhn 20:25.\x* a post.
\v 2 So I just want to ask you one thing: did you receiveВҰ126397 the \nd spiritВҰ126396\nd* by obeying all the rules, or was it by faithВҰ126401 when you heard?
\v 3 So aren't you being foolishВҰ126403? HavingВҰ126405 begunВҰ126405 in the \nd spiritВҰ126406\nd*, now you \add people\add* are focussing back on bodily discipline.
\v 4 You vainly endured so many thingsвҖ”it was vain wasn't it?
\v 5 SoВҰ126419 the one who gave the \nd spiritВҰ126423\nd* to you and worked miraclesВҰ126426 amongВҰ126427 you, did all that come about from obeying the rules or by the faithВҰ126438 that came from hearingВҰ126437 \add the good message\add*?
\s1 The spreading of Abraham's blessing
\p
\v 6 AbrahamВҰ126440\x + \xo 3:6: \xt Gen 15:6; Rom 4:3.\x* believedВҰ126441 in \nd GodВҰ126443\nd* andВҰ126444 was declared guiltless as a result.
\v 7 So now anyone who exercises faithВҰ126455 is a descendant of AbrahamВҰ126460.\x + \xo 3:7: \xt Rom 4:16.\x*
\v 8 \x + \xo 3:8: \xt Gen 12:3.\x*The \add writers of the\add* scripturesВҰ126464 foresawВҰ126461 that \nd GodВҰ126473\nd* was going to make non-Jews guiltless through faithВҰ126467 when he promised to AbrahamВҰ126476 that all the nationsВҰ126483 would be blessedВҰ126478 through him,
\v 9 so those who have faithВҰ126487 \add that Yeshua is the messiah\add* will be blessed just as AbrahamВҰ126492 was blessed for believingВҰ126491 \add God\add*.
\p
\v 10 All those who strive to be saved by obeying the law are underВҰ126499 a curse, becauseВҰ126503 it's written that вҖҳeveryone is cursed who doesn't live by and fulfil everything that's been written down in the law scrollВҰ126519вҖҷ.\x + \xo 3:10: \xt Deu 27:26 (LXX).\x*
\v 11 It's clear that the law can't make anyoneВҰ126529 guiltless \add вүҲin \nd God\nd*'s view\add*, becauseВҰ126535 \add it's written that\add* вҖҳthose who are guiltless will live by faithВҰ126539вҖҷ.\x + \xo 3:11: \xt Hab 2:4.\x*
\v 12 And the law doesn't produce faithВҰ126547, butВҰ126548 вҖҳthe person who obeys these things is the one who will liveвҖҷ.\x + \xo 3:12: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*
\p
\v 13 The \nd messiahВҰ126557\nd* saved us from the law's curse by becomingВҰ126565 the curse for our sake, becauseВҰ126569 it's writtenВҰ126570, вҖҳ\nd anyoneВҰ126557\nd* who's hung on a treeВҰ126577 is cursedвҖҷ.\x + \xo 3:13: \xt Deu 21:23.\x*
\v 14 He \add paid the price for us\add* so that the blessingВҰ126583 for AbrahamВҰ126585 would also reach the non-Jews through the \nd messiahВҰ126588 Yeshua\nd* and we'd \add all\add* be able to receiveВҰ126598 the \nd spiritВҰ126597\nd* through faithВҰ126601.
\s1 The law didn't annul the promise
\rem /s1 The Law and the Promise
\rem /s1 The Promise to Abraham
\rem /s1 The Law and God's Promises
\p
\v 15 BrothersВҰ126602 andВҰ126602 sistersВҰ126602, consider our human ways: once an agreement has been accepted, one party can't just rejectВҰ126613 it or add conditionsВҰ126615.
\v 16 The promisesВҰ126621 were given to AbrahamВҰ126618 andВҰ126622 to hisВҰ126625 offspring. It doesn't say вҖҳoffsprings (plural)вҖҷ butВҰ126634 is only referring to the one who's the \nd messiahВҰ126644\nd*.
\v 17 SoВҰ126646 what I'm telling you is that the agreement \add with Abraham\add* that was previouslyВҰ126649 ratifiedВҰ126649 by \nd GodВҰ126652\nd* was not annulledВҰ126665 430 yearsВҰ126661 later\x + \xo 3:17: \xt Exo 12:40.\x* when the law was given \add to Mosheh\add*, andВҰ126659 nor was the promiseВҰ126670 nullifiedВҰ126668,
\v 18 \x + \xo 3:18: \xt Rom 4:14.\x*becauseВҰ126672 if the inheritanceВҰ126677 now came by obeying the law, then it could no longerВҰ126678 be the result of the promise, but \nd GodВҰ126688\nd* had already grantedВҰ126686 it to AbrahamВҰ126683 via the promise.
\rem /s1 The Purpose of the Law
\v 19 SoВҰ126690 what was the law for then? Because of sinfulness, it was addedВҰ126697 untilВҰ126698 the promisedВҰ126705 descendant would comeВҰ126701. It was directedВҰ126706 throughВҰ126707 messengersВҰ126708 and entrusted to \add Mosheh as\add* a mediatorВҰ126712.
\v 20 You don'tВҰ126717 need a mediatorВҰ126715 if there's only one partyВҰ126716 involved, andВҰ126714 \nd GodВҰ126721\nd* is one.
\s1 Coming of age for the inheritance
\rem /s1 The Purpose of the Law
\p
\v 21 SoВҰ126725 does the law oppose God's promisesВҰ126729? Certainly not, becauseВҰ126735 if the law was able to giveВҰ126741 lifeВҰ126741, you could becomeВҰ126733 guiltless by obeying the law.
\v 22 The scripturesВҰ126757 \add explain that\add* \nd everyoneВҰ126768\nd* is imprisonedВҰ126755 by sinВҰ126761 so that by faithВҰ126766 in \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ126768\nd*, the promiseВҰ126764 could be granted to those who believeВҰ126771.
\p
\v 23 Before faith could come, we were guardedВҰ126780 underВҰ126778 the lawвҖ”imprisonedВҰ126782 so that faith could be revealedВҰ126787.
\rem /s1 God's Children through Faith
\v 24 So the law was ourВҰ126792 tutorВҰ126791 until the \nd messiahВҰ126796\nd* came so that weВҰ126800 could then be made guiltless by faithВҰ126799,
\v 25 and now that we've comeВҰ126801 to faithВҰ126804, we're no longerВҰ126805 underВҰ126806 our tutorВҰ126807.
\rem /s1 Sons of God
\p
\v 26 So you're all \nd God\nd*'s children throughВҰ126815 faithВҰ126817 in the \nd messiahВҰ126819\nd*, \nd Yeshua\nd*,
\v 27 becauseВҰ126823 \nd everyoneВҰ126825\nd* who's been immersedВҰ126826 \add to obey\add* the messiah is now cloaked in the messiah.
\v 28 So there's no Jew or GreekВҰ126835, no slaveВҰ126839 or free person, no male or femaleВҰ126846, becauseВҰ126849 you're all \add identified\add* as being in the \nd messiahВҰ126854\nd*, \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\v 29 \x + \xo 3:29: \xt Rom 4:13.\x*And if you're in the \nd messiahВҰ126860\nd*, thenВҰ126858 you're now Abraham's descendant, andВҰ126858 so you're heirsВҰ126870 of that promiseВҰ126869.
\c 4
\rem /s1 Life under the law
\p
\v 1 ButВҰ126872 as longВҰ126874 as the heir is underage, he's no wealthier than a slaveВҰ126882 (even though he'll \add become\add* the masterВҰ126883),
\v 2 butВҰ126890 he's underВҰ126887 guardiansВҰ126888 and managersВҰ126891 untilВҰ126892 he reaches the age that his fatherВҰ126897 specified.
\v 3 That's how it is with usвҖ”when we were infantsВҰ126903 we were enslavedВҰ126911 by this world'sВҰ126908 principlesВҰ126906,
\v 4 butВҰ126913 at the appointed timeВҰ126918, \nd GodВҰ126921\nd* sentВҰ126919 hisВҰ126924 son down to be given birth to by a womanВҰ126927 and to live underВҰ126929 \add Mosheh's\add* law
\v 5 \x + \xo 4:5-7: \xt Rom 8:15-17.\x*so that he could buy back those enslaved underВҰ126933 the law and they could now be adoptedВҰ126938 as children \add with an inheritance\add*.
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ126941 becauseВҰ126940 you're now children, \nd GodВҰ126946\nd* sent hisВҰ126951 son's \nd spiritВҰ126948\nd* down into ourВҰ126955 heartsВҰ126954 as we call out, вҖҳFather, father.вҖҷ
\v 7 Now you'reВҰ126963 no longerВҰ126962 slavesВҰ126964, butВҰ126965 children \add with full rights\add*, andВҰ126968 as children, heirs of God's \add promise\add*.
\s1 Paul's concerns about their faith
\rem /s1 Paul's Concern for the Galatians
\rem /s1 Paul Reproves the Galatians
\p
\v 8 When you didn'tВҰ126979 know \nd GodВҰ126981\nd*, you servedВҰ126982 others who aren'tВҰ126979 really godsВҰ126988 at all.
\v 9 ButВҰ126994 now that you do know God, or ratherВҰ126993 now that God knows you, why would you turn back again to useless and inferior beliefs, to serve them all over again?
\v 10 You \add people\add* observeВҰ127015 \add special\add* holidays and \add certain\add* monthsВҰ127018 and seasonsВҰ127020 and yearsВҰ127022.
\v 11 I worry that maybe I'veВҰ127028 wasted my time helping you.
\p
\v 12 I implore you to becomeВҰ127032 like me, brothersВҰ127039 andВҰ127039 sistersВҰ127039, becauseВҰ127035 I'm also just like you. You haven't wrongedВҰ127044 me in any way,
\v 13 but you know that it was a result of my fleshlyВҰ127051 weakness that I originally preachedВҰ127052 the goodВҰ127052 messageВҰ127052 to you.\f + \fr 4:13 \ft Scholars are unclear whether this might mean something like ill health, poor eyesight (see v15), or even a moral weakness, so we've left it as ambiguous in the translation as it is in the original.\f*
\v 14 Yet you didn'tВҰ127066 mock or despise me, \add brothers andВҰ127056 sisters,\add* for this trialВҰ127058 of myВҰ127065 fleshВҰ127064, butВҰ127056 rather you received me as God's messengerВҰ127072 like you might have received the \nd messiahВҰ127077 Yeshua\nd* himself.
\v 15 SoВҰ127081 whereВҰ127080 are your generous attitudes now? I know that back then, you would have almost dug your own eyesВҰ127093 out to give them to me.
\v 16 Have I now becomeВҰ127103 yourВҰ127102 enemyВҰ127101 just because I told you \add people\add* the truthВҰ127104?
\p
\v 17 Those \add others\add* have worked hard to \add try to win\add* you \add over\add*, but not for good \add reasons\add*вҖ”they want to cut you off so that you'll be enthusiastic about them.
\v 18 It's good to be enthusiastic about things that are alwaysВҰ127124 good, and not only at the times when I'm with you, \add brothers and sisters\add*.
\v 19 MyВҰ127136 dear ones, who I'm againВҰ127138 labouringВҰ127139 with in childbirth untilВҰ127140 the \nd messiahВҰ127144\nd* becomes part of youВҰ127146,
\v 20 I wanted to be there with you now, and to speak quite differently than this, becauseВҰ127158 I'm puzzled about you.
\s1 The free line and the slaves
\rem /s1 Freedom through Christ
\rem /s1 The Allegory of Hagar and Sarah
\rem /s1 The Example of Hagar and Sarah
\rem /s1 Abraham's Two Children
\rem /s1 Hagar and Sarah
\p
\v 21 Are you \add people\add* who are underВҰ127165 the law tellingВҰ127162 me that you're not even hearingВҰ127173 what the law is?
